svg.title: GAS-img
svg.text: People can get the small cube near the subway station with soil brick and seeds inside. When you touch it, your finger prints are recorded to set up your own profile online. Hence the seeds belong to you. After the seeds sprout-ing, more space are needed. Then the cube will instruct you to get the “starter kit”

“Starter kit” includes two parts, the part above is used as a flowerpot made by biodegradable materials, the part beneath is tool kit. When the part above are transplanted to the soil, the tool kit can be carried separately.

The indicator inserted to soil is connected with the network to show the condition of your plants. When it was unlocked by your finger prints, you can also see your plants through holographic projec-tion even in your work place.

Closed plants become a easy start point of socializing. People share their tools, fruits as well as there life experience. In this tiny community, people get the sense of belonging from the contact with land and other people.
